description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Trust&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Cambridge University Hospitals (CUH) NHS Foundation Trust comprises Addenbrooke’s Hospital and the Rosie Hospital in Cambridge. With over 11000 staff and over 1100 beds the priorities of the Trust focus on a quality service which is all about people – patients, staff and partners. Recognised as providing ‘outstanding’ care to our patients and rated ‘Good’ overall by the Care Quality Commissioner, is testament to the skill and dedication of the people who work here. CUH’s values – Together- safe, kind, excellent – are at the heart of patient care, defining the way all staff work and behave. The Trust provides accessible high-quality healthcare for the local people of Cambridge, together with specialist services, dealing with rare or complex conditions for a regional, national and international population.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Specialist Craftsperson (Electrical) within the Estates Operations department.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have core specialist skills in electrical services, ideally in LV, HV, distribution, generators, fire alarm systems, nurse call systems and Building Management Systems. You will be able to carry out activities which are complex and/or non-routine to involve fault finding, installation and maintenance.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will hold a BTEC HNC/HND/Approved Apprenticeship, City and Guilds or NVQ III Technician&#39;s Certificate or equivalent qualification in a relevant topic.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There will be a requirement to carry out administration duties to include updating worksheets and job tickets, data inputting and completion of Planned Preventative Maintenance worksheets with the ability to communicate verbally, by phone and in writing to Senior Management and clinical users throughout the Trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This vacancy will close on 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are due to be held on 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits to you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer development opportunities and a wide range of benefits including on-site leisure facilities, shopping concourse, day nurseries and access to a great transport system with easy access to airports and rail travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details of our fantastic benefits please refer to the attachment below - CUH Benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note if you would like to discuss the required hours of this role further, you should approach the contact given. In some cases alternative working hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from the Armed Forces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
